    <div class="slide">
        <h1>Best Practices for Data Security with AI</h1>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Data Minimization:</strong> Only use the data that is strictly necessary for the AI task.</li>
            <li><strong>Anonymization and Pseudonymization:</strong> Remove or mask identifying information where possible.</li>
            <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> Limit access to AI systems and the data they use.</li>
            <li><strong>Regular Audits:</strong> Monitor AI systems for unusual activity or potential vulnerabilities.</li>
            <li><strong>Employee Training:</strong> Educate staff on responsible AI usage and data security protocols.</li>
        </ul>
        <img src="security-best-practices.png" alt="Security Best Practices Graphic">
